sec.p:
The policies formulated by different countries can be categorized into three development stages:
For countries where energy storage has not yet been promoted or has just started commercialization, energy storage is included in the national strategic planning, and the government starts setting out the energy storage development route;
For countries where energy storage already has a certain industrial scale, tax, and subsidy preferential policies are promoted;
For countries where energy storage has developed deeply into the industrial auxiliary market, they will open up the regional electricity market.
